spettro: spettro (music player with logarithmic spectrum display)
spettro:
spettro: Most spectrographic music players use a linear frequency axis,
spettro: which dedicates the top half of the display to the top octave
spettro: (11025Hz-22050Hz at CD-quality), the next quarter of the screen to the
spettro: penultimate octave and so on, leaving all the musically interesting
spettro: information crushed into the bottom few rows of the graphic.
spettro:
spettro: Spettro has a logarithmic frequency axis, which allocates the same
spettro: amount of space to each octave.
